1
00:00:00,375 --> 00:00:03,750
My name is Faraj Salamah from
the town of Tabqa in Raqqa Province

2
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:06,333
I am 27 years old

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Married and have one daughter

4
00:00:10,916 --> 00:00:12,500
At the beginning of 2016

5
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:17,500
I was working in agriculture in rural Tabqa

6
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:23,166
Things were relatively stable in the area

7
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:29,375
On February 19 2016, a Friday

8
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:32,625
The situation was normal

9
00:00:34,708 --> 00:00:36,500
I was getting ready for Friday prayer

10
00:00:37,916 --> 00:00:40,541
When I was about to leave the bathroom

11
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:43,666
Preparing to go to the mosque

12
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:45,875
I heard movement outside the bathroom

13
00:00:46,083 --> 00:00:47,875
Then someone knocked on the door

14
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,000
He told me not to come out

15
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:54,166
I waited for about half an hour

16
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:59,291
I noticed armed men

17
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:02,083
From ISIS inside the house

18
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:04,458
I heard weapons and wireless devices

19
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:06,333
It became clear it was a raid

20
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:09,041
Things were not normal

21
00:01:10,416 --> 00:01:15,291
After half an hour someone ordered me to leave the bathroom

22
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:18,791
Everyone outside was armed

23
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:22,875
They ordered me to stand in front of the house

24
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:26,208
And I found my brothers outside too

25
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:29,375
Sitting on chairs while ISIS members searched the house

26
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,916
I realized the village was surrounded and being searched

27
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,958
Every now and then an ISIS vehicle arrived

28
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:38,500
Bringing two or three of my cousins

29
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:39,833
Then leaving again

30
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,500
We stayed until the afternoon prayer

31
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:45,958
For nearly three hours or more

32
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:51,625
Then ISIS members put us in vehicles

33
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:56,000
The first building we entered was the Islamic Police base

34
00:01:57,458 --> 00:02:02,333
Inside I saw relatives from a nearby village

35
00:02:02,916 --> 00:02:05,833
Some of my brothers had gone to Friday prayers before us

36
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:07,625
So they followed them to the mosque

37
00:02:08,375 --> 00:02:11,125
And while they were praying, they were all arrested

38
00:02:13,041 --> 00:02:14,791
They put us all together

39
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:18,333
Every 10 minutes cars arrived

40
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:22,458
Taking several people away to unknown destinations

41
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:25,083
The cars kept coming

42
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:28,125
We were about 30 people or more

43
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,291
All brothers and cousins

44
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:33,833
Finally, it was our turn

45
00:02:33,958 --> 00:02:37,291
We got in blindfolded, not knowing where we were going

46
00:02:39,416 --> 00:02:41,000
We drove a short distance

47
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:44,291
I believe still within Tabqa

48
00:02:45,416 --> 00:02:49,458
When we entered, we realized it was the Bourj (Tower) Prison of ISIS

49
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:54,458
We got out of the vehicle and lined up facing the wall

50
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:56,833
Beside other blindfolded prisoners I could sense nearby

51
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,833
It was completely silent

52
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:03,083
They began opening doors and distributing the prisoners

53
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:07,541
They placed two or three in each
solitary cell because of the overcrowding

54
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,166
I was put in a solitary cell too

55
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:12,166
With two of my cousins

56
00:03:13,916 --> 00:03:18,500
Next to us were other solitary cells, and opposite were group cells

57
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,875
They started taking prisoners for interrogation

58
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:26,125
To collect personal information about us

59
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:27,750
Then returning us

60
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,458
During the first day, no one was taken for interrogation

61
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:35,208
After 2:30 a.m.

62
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:41,541
We heard noise as they brought in a large number of prisoners

63
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:46,083
We could see through the cell door

64
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:52,125
Watching through the small window, we saw the corridor

65
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:56,041
We saw they had arrested many young men

66
00:03:56,916 --> 00:04:00,041
Blindfolded in the same way as us

67
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:02,750
Lined up against the wall in the corridor

68
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:04,791
Then they started distributing them

69
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:06,666
They put them with us

70
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:10,166
It turned out they were our relatives from Jarnieh, rural Tabqa

71
00:04:11,458 --> 00:04:12,291
We recognized each other

72
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,291
It was the first time I had seen them

73
00:04:16,375 --> 00:04:17,458
After two days

74
00:04:18,875 --> 00:04:20,458
They transferred me to another cell

75
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,500
It was not solitary

76
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:26,666
There were around 10 or 11 people

77
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,208
All of them my relatives

78
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:32,125
We started asking each other about our family members

79
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:35,041
I asked about my brothers and father
because I didn’t know where they were

80
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:38,666
But I could hear their voices from inside the solitary cells

81
00:04:38,875 --> 00:04:41,000
Even though our group cell was far from theirs

82
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:46,750
Located in a different section outside the solitary area

83
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:49,708
To reach it, you had to pass through the kitchen

84
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:51,416
Then another room

85
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:54,041
Before arriving at the large group cell

86
00:04:56,166 --> 00:04:58,708
One of my relatives told me he had been with my father

87
00:04:58,875 --> 00:04:59,916
And reassured me that he was fine

88
00:05:00,041 --> 00:05:03,333
But we still didn’t know why we had been arrested or for what reason

89
00:05:05,041 --> 00:05:07,708
Every week

90
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,666
They would select two or three people and release them

91
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:13,916
We were in contact with the group cell next to us

92
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:17,458
The cell door was confusing in layout

93
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,375
It didn’t open to the hallway but faced a wall

94
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:25,750
We spoke with them through the electrical outlet

95
00:05:25,916 --> 00:05:27,833
Where one of my brothers and cousins were

96
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,583
I kept in touch with them constantly

97
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:33,791
I stayed for 27 days

98
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:35,916
In that group cell

99
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:39,833
Until only my two cousins and I remained

100
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,500
The rest were released

101
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:48,666
Without knowing which of my relatives and
brothers were still in the remaining group cells

102
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:50,916
I was called in for interrogation

103
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:54,125
To be asked about my brother Ibrahim

104
00:05:54,916 --> 00:05:57,125
Whom I thought had been detained with us

105
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:00,125
But I hadn’t heard his voice

106
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:01,541
So I realized they hadn’t arrested him

107
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:04,916
I answered that I didn’t know and that he was in Tabqa

108
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:08,666
And that we usually went together to Friday prayers

109
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:11,791
But I didn’t see him because you arrived before the prayer

110
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:14,083
And took us away before it started

111
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:19,708
He took me to the disciplinary cell (solitary cell)

112
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:21,916
And began asking what weapons I owned

113
00:06:22,041 --> 00:06:23,208
I told him I had no weapons at all

114
00:06:24,166 --> 00:06:26,583
I said the only weapon was the hunting rifle

115
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:28,541
That you found in the house

116
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:31,708
He repeated his question, claiming we had buried weapons

117
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:34,125
Accusing me of belonging to the Free Syrian Army

118
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:35,583
Because my brother was with the Free Syrian Army

119
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:37,958
I told him my brother

120
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:42,250
Is responsible for himself, and we have nothing to do with him

121
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,458
He said, No problem then

122
00:06:43,541 --> 00:06:44,666
And took me to a room

123
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,250
Not a normal room

124
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:47,583
It was smaller than a solitary cell

125
00:06:47,666 --> 00:06:50,166
They called it the disciplinary cell

126
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:53,041
About 60 centimeters wide

127
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,291
And about one and a half meters long

128
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,833
I stayed there for four days

129
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:00,750
They gave us food through the door

130
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:04,333
And at prayer times, they allowed us out only for ablution

131
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:07,166
After four days, he brought me back for interrogation

132
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,291
And asked what new information I had this time

133
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:10,750
I told him I knew nothing

134
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:13,041
When I entered the disciplinary cell

135
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,958
There was someone next to me

136
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,625
From Safira

137
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:21,291
He told me, When I arrived here, your father...

138
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:24,791
Was inside this room

139
00:07:25,458 --> 00:07:27,375
They took him out and put me in his place

140
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:29,291
Then I began to hear my father’s voice

141
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:32,208
Because the disciplinary cells were in the same corridor

142
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,041
That contained the solitary and group cells

143
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,000
So I could hear my father’s voice

144
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,416
And two of my brothers

145
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:43,375
And a cousin of mine, I could hear them clearly

146
00:07:44,583 --> 00:07:47,500
That’s how I knew who remained
in prison and who had been released

147
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:49,708
Late at night

148
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:51,500
We would talk to each other

149
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:54,041
Without ISIS members noticing

150
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:57,583
Or maybe they noticed and pretended not to

151
00:07:59,041 --> 00:07:59,791
After another four days

152
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,875
He brought me back for interrogation again

153
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:03,791
The interrogator asked if I had any new statements

154
00:08:03,958 --> 00:08:06,875
I told him I’d already said everything I knew

155
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:08,291
And I had nothing new

156
00:08:09,083 --> 00:08:09,125
He put me in a solitary cell

157
00:08:11,083 --> 00:08:12,083
I entered the solitary cell

158
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:14,916
And found a young man from Daraa

159
00:08:16,416 --> 00:08:17,041
He told me

160
00:08:17,083 --> 00:08:18,791
Your brother was with me

161
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:20,750
Then they moved him to the group cell

162
00:08:21,875 --> 00:08:23,833
After midnight

163
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:26,291
I would talk with my father. He heard me and I heard him

164
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:28,791
One of my brothers was with him

165
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:32,416
And they also had no charges brought against them

166
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:34,500
Another brother was far away in a solitary cell

167
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,208
I couldn’t communicate with him well

168
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:38,916
But we could hear each other’s voices

169
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,333
And knew we were in the same prison

170
00:08:42,916 --> 00:08:45,041
My cousins were on my right and left

171
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,250
On the right and on the left

172
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,083
After three or four days

173
00:08:52,375 --> 00:08:54,708
They took one of my cousins out of the solitary cells

174
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,000
That were beside me

175
00:08:56,125 --> 00:08:59,083
And moved him to another solitary cell

176
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:01,708
Then they brought in two women

177
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:07,333
About 25 to 26 years old

178
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,291
In the prison, we communicated

179
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,541
Through the water taps

180
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:17,583
We spoke and heard each other, though not clearly

181
00:09:19,416 --> 00:09:21,833
ISIS had arrested them

182
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:23,791
For walking repeatedly near the base

183
00:09:23,958 --> 00:09:25,291
Accusing them of filming

184
00:09:25,458 --> 00:09:27,791
And sending footage to the Global Coalition Against ISIS

185
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,583
They were taken for interrogation

186
00:09:30,791 --> 00:09:32,416
After midnight

187
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:34,833
We could hear the voices of the women and the torture

188
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:39,125
We endured and prayed, saying, God is sufficient
for us, and He is the best disposer of affairs

189
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,208
Then they would be brought back

190
00:09:41,416 --> 00:09:44,916
So exhausted they couldn’t even talk to us

191
00:09:45,458 --> 00:09:47,625
We couldn’t communicate with them properly

192
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,583
After a while

193
00:09:51,083 --> 00:09:53,750
They took out my cousin who was on the left side

194
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:55,375
And moved him to another solitary cell

195
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:56,583
Then they brought women again

196
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,250
And placed them in the solitary cell next to mine

197
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:02,375
So I ended up between two solitary cells holding women

198
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,125
With the women detained the last time

199
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:06,000
There were young children with them

200
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:09,625
They took a child from one of the women

201
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:11,708
For about a week

202
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,875
We couldn’t sleep or eat

203
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:17,875
Because of the woman’s cries over her baby’s separation

204
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,625
Who I think was an infant

205
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:20,750
Less than one year old
